## IF THINGS GO WRONG

### "CheXpert training doesn't converge"
- Try learning rate 3e-4 instead of 1e-4
- Use pretrained=True (ImageNet weights)
- Verify labels are correct (print first 10 samples)
- Try training centrally first (no FL) to establish ceiling

### "PTB-XL AUC is very low (<0.80)"
- Check signal normalization (zero mean, unit variance per lead)
- Verify label mapping from SCP codes to superclasses
- Try learning rate 5e-4
- Train centrally first to debug the 1D model

### "Proof generation is too slow even for INT8"
- Reduce the number of operations checked (sample instead of checking all)
- Optimize the LUT lookup (use a Python dict/set, not list search)
- Profile with cProfile to find bottlenecks

### "Out of memory during FL training"
- Reduce batch_size to 16 or 8
- Use gradient accumulation over 2-4 mini-batches
- Reduce number of simultaneous clients in memory (serialize instead of parallel)

### "Results don't match paper's original claims"
- This is EXPECTED. The original paper used formula-derived numbers.
- Real numbers will differ. That's fine — report what you actually measure.
- The story (TeleZK-FL is much faster than standard ZK with minimal accuracy loss) should still hold.
- Update ALL numbers in the paper to match reality.